<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E67FFE948A75250FE0CF90C" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E67FFE948A75250FEAFFA64" blockId="41.[151,721,1368,1428]" box="[151,266,1404,1428]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E67FFE948905250FEA4FA64" box="[160,257,1404,1428]" captionStart="PLATE 9" captionStartId="37.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,211,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-108@37.[215,1371,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="PLATE 9. Male genitalia. A. Aphelopus sabahnus from China, Taiwan. B. A. spadiceus from China, Sichuan. C. A. taiwanensis, holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. A. thai, holotype (from Olmi 2008c). E. A. wushensis, holotype (from Olmi 2010). F. A. xanthopus from China, Yunnan. G. A. zonalis sp. nov., holotype. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, B and C, 0.17mm for D, 0.13 mm for E, 0.14 mm for Fand G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278398/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Plate 9G</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E67FFE948A752EFFB7FF927" blockId="41.[151,1436,1475,1932]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E67FFE948A752EFFE35FA2C" bold="true" box="[151,400,1475,1500]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E67FFE94AAD52E8FD5CFA2B" box="[669,761,1476,1500]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. Completely testaceous, except metanotum and dorsal and posterior surface of propodeum darkened. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 4:4:4.5:5:5:5:5:5:4.5:7. Head dull, granulated; frontal line complete; occipital carina complete; POL = 7; OL = 4; OOL = 3; OPL = 2.5; TL = 4; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli shorter than OL (2:4). Scutum and scutellum dull, granulated. Notauli hardly visible, incomplete, reaching approximately 0.4 length of scutum. Metanotum shiny, unsculptured. Propodeum with dorsal surface dull, reticulate rugose; posterior surface reticulate rugose, with two longitudinal keels and medianl area shiny and partly smooth. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands. Basivolsella (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E67FFE949005193FE34F927" box="[304,401,1727,1751]" captionStart="PLATE 9" captionStartId="37.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,211,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-108@37.[215,1371,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="PLATE 9. Male genitalia. A. Aphelopus sabahnus from China, Taiwan. B. A. spadiceus from China, Sichuan. C. A. taiwanensis, holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. A. thai, holotype (from Olmi 2008c). E. A. wushensis, holotype (from Olmi 2010). F. A. xanthopus from China, Yunnan. G. A. zonalis sp. nov., holotype. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, B and C, 0.17mm for D, 0.13 mm for E, 0.14 mm for Fand G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278398/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Plate 9G</figureCitation>
) with one subdistal bristle, without outer basal process. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E67FFE948F751C8FE0CF90C" blockId="41.[151,1436,1475,1932]" box="[199,425,1764,1788]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E67FFE948F751C8FE80F90C" bold="true" box="[199,293,1764,1788]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
